      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(install): harden stdin consumers to prevent pipe corruption in curl | bash",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen the OpenClaw installer is piped via `curl | bash`, child processes spawned\nunder `gum spin` can inherit the script stream as stdin. Gum v0.17.0 sets the\nwrapped command's stdin to `os.Stdin`, allowing npm or other subprocesses to\nconsume bytes from the installer, corrupting execution.\n\nAdditionally, fallback paths (when gum raw mode fails or gum is unavailable)\nredirected stdin unconditionally from `/dev/null`, breaking interactive commands\nlike Homebrew installation prompts when the script is run directly.\n\n## Fix\n\n**P1: Redirect gum-wrapped command stdin.** The normal `gum spin` path now\nredirects stdin from `/dev/null`, isolating child commands from the piped\nscript stream:\n\n```bash\n\"$GUM\" spin --spinner dot --title \"$title\" -- \"$@\" < /dev/null >\"$gum_out\" 2>\"$gum_err\"\n```\n\n**P2: Conditional stdin redirect for fallback paths.** All fallback paths\n(gum raw-mode fallback, non-gum fallback, `run_quiet_step` shell-function\npath) now check `is_non_interactive_shell` before redirecting stdin:\n\n```bash\nif is_non_interactive_shell; then\n    \"$@\" < /dev/null\nelse\n    \"$@\"\nfi\n```\n\nThis preserves terminal stdin for interactive commands (e.g., Homebrew prompts)\nwhen running `bash install.sh` directly, while protecting against pipe\nconsumption when piped.\n\n**P2: Labeler changes removed.** The size-label best-effort handling has been\nremoved from this PR to keep it focused on installer stdin safety. It belongs\nin a separate PR.\n\n## Behavior proof\n\n**Environment:** macOS arm64, gum v0.17.0 (the version that passes os.Stdin to child commands)\n\n### P1: gum spin stdin redirect verified\n\n```\nBefore (upstream):\n  \"$GUM\" spin --spinner dot --title \"$title\" -- \"$@\" >\"$gum_out\" 2>\"$gum_err\"\n\nAfter (this PR, line 453):\n  if \"$GUM\" spin --spinner dot --title \"$title\" -- \"$@\" < /dev/null >\"$gum_out\" 2>\"$gum_err\"\n```\n\n### Functional: piped mode stdin redirect\n\nSimulating `curl | bash` scenario (stdin is a pipe):\n\n```\n$ echo \"pipe_content\" | bash -c '...'\nis_non_interactive_shell: true (stdin is a pipe)\nOK: stdin was empty (redirected from /dev/null)\nResult: 0\n```\n\n### Functional: gum spin child command isolation\n\n```\n$ echo \"pipe_content\" | gum spin --spinner dot --title \"Testing\" -- cat /dev/stdin < /dev/null\nOK: child command got empty stdin (pipe content was not consumed)\n```\n\n### P2: interactive mode stdin preservation\n\nWhen running directly (not piped), `is_non_interactive_shell` returns false,\nso commands get terminal stdin for interactive prompts (e.g., Homebrew):\n\n```\n$ bash install.sh  # stdin is a terminal\nis_non_interactive_shell: false (stdin preserved for interactive commands)\n```\n\n### Test results\n\n```\n44 passed, 1 failed (pre-existing upstream issue unrelated to stdin handling)\n```\n\nThe failing test (`does not emit before args when npmrc min-release-age computes\na before cutoff`) is an upstream test that also fails on main.\n\n## Files changed\n\n- `scripts/install.sh`: stdin redirect fixes\n- `test/scripts/install-sh.test.ts`: updated test assertions\n- `.github/workflows/labeler.yml`: reverted to upstream (changes removed from this PR)",
        "branch": "fix/install-stdin-tty-safety",
